Text.Value: Grymforge - I ran into some trouble, but I handled it.
Let's hope this Z'rell likes what we have to say.
Trouble in the Underdark - but I handled it.
Praise the Absolute.

EditorData.NodeContext: as a farewell - equivalent to 'god bless you'

Text.Value: That's for your superiors to know.
See for yourself.
I've infiltrated an encampment of Harpers protected by a cleric of Selûne.
My apologies. Welcome back, True Soul - what news?
Little to report. What news inside?
Nightwarden Minthara - you were not expected here.
Our path leads to Z'rell. Let us not keep her waiting.
'Welcome back'? I've never been here before.
Z'rell - fancy name. Let's put our best foot forward. Or is it best feet?
She's in the audience chamber. Go on in.
You - halt!
How delightful. The scouts reported your victory against the Harpers, but Disciple Z'rell was looking forward to hearing about it from you in person.
Minthara sent me.
More importantly, why is one of our rank on guard duty?
I knew it. Traitor!

EditorData.NodeContext: combat about to start - with that edge

Text.Value: Surprise - I'm here to take your head.
She's in the audience chamber, True Soul. Go right ahead.
To greet those of our like, and weed out those who walk where they do not belong.
My mistake - your mind tasted familiar. Where are you reporting from?
Where do you think you're going?
*Her mind attempts to connect with yours and finds - nothing. You have no tadpole, and no welcome in this place.*
If it's an audience she desires, an audience let us provide.
Glad to hear it. Z'rell will be too. The scrying eyes only see so much.
General Ketheric's advisor went off on a field trip - Z'rell's in charge 'til he gets back.
Impressive. I'm sure Z'rell will want to hear all about it.
Did she now? You'll find her inside, though you'll want to speak to Z'rell first.
*Her thoughts invade your own, hunting for recognition. Your parasite offers it, readily.*
*Her thoughts probe your own, finding - freedom. Heresy.*
In Her name.
True Soul. A pleasure. What news from the field?
Oh they will.
Well then, let's not keep her waiting.
I infiltrated a group of Harpers at an Inn, out in the shadows.
How delightful. It's you. Disciple Z'rell was looking forward to meeting the one who aided Balthazar. She was very pleased indeed to see him return with the Nightsong.
Nowhere of importance. What news inside?
Z'rell's in the audience chamber, True Soul. Go right ahead.
Great news: your imminent death.
That's what I call an invitation. Let's find Z'rell and get this caravan moving.
Leave.
I have a message from Nere. Who should I report to?

Synopsis: The guard mindmelds with player, senses their tadpole, and gladly lets them into the towers, telling them to report to Disciple Z'rell (Zuh-rELL).
